It seems that there are some problems with the combination of 
hardware (PCI/MB/SCSI) and software (drivers), making difficult 
to run linux and OS/2 on these configurations. It's not so 
clear if the problems are of PCI chipset revision,
the scsi controller, bios revision, the SCSI drivers or 
a combination of them. 

And how about the PCI compatibility interfaces between different
machines ? For sample, an AHA-2940 and a Diammond Stealth 64 PCI 
will works on a PowerPC machine or on a Alpha machine ?

I would like to know some motherboards 486/PCI with AHA-2940 
that runs Linux and OS/2. 

