I do believe that the AHA-2940 is not supported by Linux.   Adaptec
is usually pretty good about supplying drivers for OS/2.
Most Diamond cards are not supported by Linux.   A few with a Cirrus
Logic chipset are though, and I can't remember what chipset the
Stealth uses.  

For Linux hardware compatability, you might want to check out the
Hardware-HOWTO at sunsite.unc.edu (pub/Linux/docs/HOWTO, I think).
It lists all the currently supported hardware.


